column12: A WIND TURBINE BLADE
column13: A wind turbine blade is described having a serrated trailing edge. Flow straightening vanes are provided on the serrations, to prevent a lateral or side flow over the edges of the serrations, which are preferably provided at incidence to the flow over the wind turbine blade. The vanes can be formed integrally with the serrations, or attached to existing serrations as a retrofit solution. The serrations with the vanes can be provided as a trailing edge panel for attachment to the trailing edge of an existing wind turbine blade.

Pale d'éolienne
column13: La présente invention concerne une pale d'éolienne possédant un bord de fuite dentelé. Des aubes directrices d'écoulement sont disposées sur les dentelures, de manière à empêcher un écoulement latéral sur les bords des dentelures, qui sont de préférence disposées de manière incidente par rapport à l'écoulement sur la pale d'éolienne. Les aubes peuvent être formées d'un seul tenant avec les dentelures, ou attachées aux dentelures existantes en tant que solution de rattrapage. Les dentelures dotées des aubes peuvent être fournies sous la forme d'un panneau de bord de fuite pour une fixation au bord de fuite d'une pale d'éolienne existante.

column12: SPLITTER PLATE ARRANGEMENT FOR A SERRATED WIND TURBINE BLADE
column13: A wind turbine blade (10) is described having a serrated trailing edge (20). Splitter plates (106) are provided on the blade, to reduce operational noise. Each splitter plate (106) is arranged to extend at least partly into a space in between adjacent serrations. The splitter plates can be formed integrally with the serrations, or attached to existing serrations as a retrofit solution. The serrations with the splitter plates can be provided as a trailing edge panel (108) for attachment to the trailing edge of an existing wind turbine blade.

column12: WIRE CADDY
column13: A toolbox-size device contains wire spools that are supported by both a cradle and a removable axial spindle. This dual support contributes to solving several problems involved with manual wire deployment devices. Particular object spatial and size relationships can include those of the cradle, spindle, spool diameter, spool hub, arbor-opening diameter, enclosure size, and exit aperture location. This provides a solution to reliably and smoothly deploy electrical wire manually from a hand-carried device. The cradle holds spools generally in place when the axial spindle is removed to add or remove spools. The dual support system allows the use of spools with damaged flanges normally not possible with a cradle-based system.

column12: PÁ DE TURBINA EÓLICA
column13: PÁ DE TURBINA EÓLICA Uma pá de turbina eólica é descrita tendo uma borda de fuga serrilhada. As palhetas de alinhamento de fluxo são proporcionadas nas serrilhas, para evitar um fluxo lateral sobre as bordas das serrilhas, que são preferencialmente proporcionadas em incidência ao fluxo sobre a pá de turbina eólica. As palhetas podem ser formadas integralmente com as serrilhas, ou ligadas a serrilhas existentes como uma solução retro adaptadora. As serrilhas com as palhetas podem ser proporcionadas como um painel de borda de fuga para anexar a borda de fuga de uma pá de turbina de vento existente.

column12: A WIND TURBINE BLADE
column13: A wind turbine blade is described wherein the blade has an adjustable flow modulating profile at the trailing edge of the blade. The profile has at least one array of projecting flow modulation elements which can act to modulate airflow and associated turbulent noise at the trailing edge. The elements of the array can be adjusted during operation of a wind turbine having such a blade to provide for controlled noise modulation, which does not require complicated redesign and/or retrofitting procedures. Examples of adjustments include translational movement of the array of elements, variation of element shape, flexibility, etc. The adjustment may be passively and/or actively controlled.

Noise reducer for a wind turbine rotor blade
column13: The present invention relates to a wind turbine rotor blade assembly comprising a rotor blade and a noise reducer ( 70 ) configured on the rotor blade. The noise reducer ( 70 ) comprises a plurality of aligned spine members ( 72 ), each spine member having a length and comprising a first section ( 74 ) extending along a first part of the length of the spine member, and a second section ( 76 ) extending along a second part of the length of the spine member, wherein the first section ( 74 ) has a higher stiffness than the second section ( 76 ).

column12: Compsizione per l'uso in un trattamento contro l'infertilità
A WIND TURBINE BLADE COMPRISING A TRAILING EDGE NOISE REDUCING DEVICE
column13: This invention relates to a noise reducing device and a wind turbine blade comprises such a noise reducing device. The noise reducing device comprises a number of noise reducing elements projecting from a base part. A plurality of airflow modifying elements are attached to or integrated into the noise reducing elements. The airflow modifying elements extend from a local first end to a local second end along at least one of the first and second side surfaces. The airflow modifying elements has a height of no more than two-thirds of the boundary layer thickness and spacing of no more than one-thirds of the boundary layer thickness. The noise reducing elements are preferably serrations. The airflow modifying elements are preferably vanes projecting perpendicularly from the side surface of the noise reducing elements.

Una pala de turbina eólica que comprende un dispositivo de reducción de ruido en el borde de salida
column13: Esta invención se refiere a un dispositivo reductor de ruido y una pala de turbina eólica comprende dicho dispositivo reductor de ruido. El dispositivo reductor de ruido comprende varios elementos reductores de ruido que sobresalen de una parte de base. Una pluralidad de elementos modificadores del flujo de aire están unidos o integrados en los elementos reductores de ruido. Los elementos modificadores del flujo de aire se extienden desde un primer extremo local hasta un segundo extremo local a lo largo de al menos una de las superficies laterales primera y segunda. Los elementos modificadores del flujo de aire tienen una altura de no más de dos tercios del espesor de la capa límite y una separación de no más de un tercio del espesor de la capa límite. Los elementos reductores de ruido son preferentemente dentados. Los elementos modificadores del flujo de aire son preferiblemente paletas que se proyectan perpendicularmente desde la superficie lateral de los elementos reductores de ruido. column12: A WIND TURBINE BLADE AND A METHOD OF OPERATING SUCH A WIND TURBINE BLADE
column13: This invention relates to an airfoil modifying device, a wind turbine blade and a method of modifying an airfoil profile of the wind turbine blade. The airfoil modifying device comprises a deformable element connected to a filler element, both configured to deform between a retracted position and an extended position. A WIND TURBINE BLADE COMPRISING A TRAILING EDGE NOISE REDUCING DEVICE
column13: This invention relates to a noise reducing device and a wind turbine blade comprises such a noise reducing device. The noise reducing device comprises a number of noise reducing elements projecting from a base part. A plurality of airflow modifying elements are attached to or integrated into the noise reducing elements. The airflow modifying elements extend from a local first end to a local second end along at least one of the first and second side surfaces. The airflow modifying elements has a height of no more than two-thirds of the boundary layer thickness and spacing of no more than one-thirds of the boundary layer thickness. The noise reducing elements are preferably serrations. The airflow modifying elements are preferably vanes projecting perpendicularly from the side surface of the noise reducing elements.

column13: esta invenção se refere a um dispositivo de redução de ruído e uma pá de turbina eólica compreende tal dispositivo de redução de ruído. o dispositivo de redução de ruído compreende vários elementos redutores de ruído que se projetam de uma parte de base. uma pluralidade de elementos modificadores de fluxo de ar é fixada ou integrada aos elementos redutores de ruído. os elementos modificadores de fluxo de ar se estendem de uma primeira extremidade local até uma segunda extremidade local ao longo de pelo menos uma dentre a primeira e a segunda superfícies laterais. os elementos modificadores de fluxo de ar têm uma altura de não mais de dois terços da espessura da camada limítrofe e espaçamento de não mais de um terço da espessura da camada limítrofe. os elementos redutores de ruído são preferencialmente serrilhados. os elementos modificadores de fluxo de ar são preferencialmente palhetas que se projetam perpendicularmente a partir da superfície lateral dos elementos redutores de ruído.

column13: This invention relates to a noise reducing device, a wind turbine blade comprises such a noise reducing device, a method of retrofitted a noise reducing device, and a method of manufacturing such a noise reducing device. The noise reducing device comprises first noise reducing elements projecting from a base part having a third surface towards a second end. Second noise reducing elements are attached to the third surface and projects along the first noise reducing elements towards the second end. The first noise reducing elements are preferably serrations while the second noise reducing elements are bristles. The bristles projects at least into the gaps formed between adjacent serrations.

CERAMIC BIOCOMPOSITE FOR BONE REGENERATION
column13: The invention relates to a ceramic biocomposite for bone regeneration, having a pH range of between 6.5 and 8.5, with an initial plasticity that allows the biocomposite to be easily moulded in situ and to set after 7 minutes, meaning that it can remain at the indicated location during the healing process. In addition, the biocomposite has demonstrated an ability to stimulate bone formation in hard-to-heal wounds. The material can act alone or in combination with other types of bone graft such as autografts, homografts or xenografts which act as a vehicle, as a binding material for endosseous prostheses or as a covering for endosseous implants or prostheses.

column12: A WIND TURBINE BLADE HAVING DEPLOYABLE AERODYNAMIC DEVICES
column13: A wind turbine blade is described, as well as a trailing edge plate for a wind turbine blade. A flexible flow modulation device, e.g. an acoustic flap or a plurality of serrations, is arranged at the trailing edge of a wind turbine blade, wherein the flexible device is coupled to at least one aerodynamic device, preferably vortex generators. As the flexible device is bent by action of flow over the wind turbine blade, the at least one aerodynamic device is deployed to provide for attached flow over the bent flexible device.

column13: To provide a method for treating infertility by promoting the development of haploid blastocysts, the method being useful for women at risk of high ovarian response to regulated ovarian stimulation.SOLUTION: The present invention relates to a composition comprising menotropin (human menopausal gonadotropin or hMG) for use in the treatment of infertility by promoting the development of equiploid blastocysts, wherein the treatment includes: selecting a woman having a risk of high ovarian response to regulated ovarian stimulation which is identified, before stimulation, to have serum anti-Mullerian hormone (AMH) levels≥5.0±0.5ng/ml and total number of follicular follicles (AFC)≥10 in both ovaries; and giving the selected women a dose of 75-300 IU hMG or equivalent per day from day 1 to day 5 of treatment.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 1

column12: METHODS OF TREATING INFERTILITY
column13: FIELD: medicine; gynecology.SUBSTANCE: group of inventions can be used for treating infertility in a patient. In order to stimulate development of euploid blastocysts and for future blastocyst transfer, the method involves identification of a patient having serum level of anti-Mullerian hormone (AMN) greater than or equal to 4.7 ng/ml and the number of antral follicles (AFC) greater than or equal to 10 in both ovaries together before treatment/stimulation. Dose of 75 to 300 IU (international unit) or equivalent dose of hMG (human menopausal gonadotrophin) per day from day 1 to at least 5 days of treatment is administered. Group of inventions also refers to a method of treating infertility in a woman who does not have PCOS (polycystic ovaries syndrome) at risk of severe ovarian response to controlled ovarian stimulation.EFFECT: use of this group of inventions enables to perform assisted reproductive technology using highly purified menotropin (HP-hMG) for stimulating follicular development in controlled ovarian stimulation, especially in women at risk of severe ovarian response to controlled ovarian stimulation.14 cl, 2 dwg, 3 tbl, 2 ex

column12: Ceramic biocomposite for bone regeneration
column13: The invention relates to a ceramic biocomposite for bone regeneration, having a pH range of between 6.5 and 8.5, with an initial plasticity that allows the biocomposite to be easily moulded in situ and to set after 7 minutes, meaning that it can remain at the indicated location during the healing process. In addition, the biocomposite has demonstrated an ability to stimulate bone formation in hard-to-heal wounds. The material can act alone or in combination with other types of bone graft such as autografts, homografts or xenografts which act as a vehicle, as a binding material for endosseous prostheses or as a covering for endosseous implants or prostheses.

Sistema, método y dispositivo contador de mosquitos
column13: La presente invención proporciona un sistema, método y dispositivo contador de mosquitos. El sistema tiene un mecanismo de agitación que golpea el contenedor que contiene los mosquitos, luego se frena el mecanismo de agitación y se procede a adquirir las señales acústicas por medio de un sensor acústico o micrófono, luego los datos son enviados a un programa de computador el cual consta de una interfaz gráfica, donde el programa de computador analiza la grabación y filtra los datos y mediante un algoritmo de análisis de la onda acústica que calcula el resultado de la cantidad de mosquitos contenidos en el contenedor.

column12: WIND TURBINE BLADE WITH TIP END SERRATIONS
column13: The present invention relates to a wind turbine blade (10) comprising two or more serrations (100a, 100b, 100c) provided along a section (S) of the trailing edge (20). The section (S) extends spanwise from the tip end (14) towards the root end (16) for up to 5% of the total blade length (L). The serration (100a) closest to the tip end has a height (H) and/or width (W) greater than the respective height (H) and/or width (W) of at least one other serration (100b, 100c) in said section. The present invention also relates to a wind turbine (2) comprising at least one wind turbine blade (10) of the present invention and to a serrated panel (66).

column12: COMPOSITION FOR TREATMENT OF INFERTILITY
column13: To provide a composition and a pharmaceutical product for treatment of infertility.SOLUTION: A composition for use in treatment of infertility comprises follicle stimulating hormone (FSH), where the treatment comprises the steps of: prior to treatment, identifying a patient having variant Ser/Ser at position 680 of the FSH receptor; and administering FSH at a dose of or equivalent to more than 12 μg to 24 μg to the patient (identified as) having variant Ser/Ser at position 680 of the FSH receptor.SELECTED DRAWING: None

column12: COMPOSITION COMPRISING FSH FOR TREATMENT OF INFERTILITY
column13: A composition for use in the treatment of infertility, the composition comprising 9 to 24 pg follicle stimulating hormone (FSH), wherein the composition is for administration to a patient identified as having variant Ser/Ser at position 680 of the FSH receptor.

column12: COMPOSITION FOR TREATING INFERTILITY
column13: FIELD: medicine.SUBSTANCE: group of inventions refers to infertility treatment. Disclosed is a method of treating infertility in a patient, wherein the infertility treatment involves: (a) identification of said patient as having serum level of antimueller hormone (AMH) less than 15 pmol/l before treatment; (b) identifying said patient as having a variant Ser/Ser at position 680 of a follicle-stimulating hormone receptor (FSH) prior to treatment; and (c) administering a dose of more than 12 to 24 mcg of recombinant follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) a day or an equivalent dose to said patient. Also disclosed is another version of infertility treatment.EFFECT: group of inventions provides more effective treatment of infertility in certain patients.2 cl, 7 dwg, 3 tbl, 9 ex

column12: TRATAMIENTO PARA LA ENDOMETRIOSIS
column13: Reivindicacion 1: Una composicion farmacéutica que comprende quinagolida para el tratamiento y/o la prevencion de la endometriosis, en donde la composicion es para administracion en una dosis de 15 a 39 microgramos de quinagolida/día durante 10 a 20 días; seguida de administracion en una dosis 40 a 64 microgramos de quinagolida/día durante otros 10 a 20 días; seguida de la administracion en una dosis de 65 a 85 microgramos de quinagolida/día durante por lo menos 2 meses. Reivindicacion 4: Una composicion para uso de acuerdo con cualquier reivindicacion precedente para el tratamiento o la prevencion de la endometriosis en un sujeto que tiene, o que tiene tendencia a la, hiperprolactinemia. Reivindicacion 15: Una composicion farmacéutica que comprende quinagolida para el tratamiento y/o la prevencion del cáncer reproductivo. Reivindicacion 17: Una composicion farmacéutica que comprende quinagolida para el tratamiento de la infertilidad en un paciente que tiene endometriosis.

(udl) para o ensino e a aprendizagem da química. composto por uma maleta com duas tampas (1a, 1b), uma base central (2), um sistema de trava (3), duas plataformas (89a, 89b) e um sistema eletrônico (90a, 90b) dotado de alto-falantes (48) e uma tela sensível ao toque (151), o produto permite que estudantes sem deficiência, da educação especial ou com necessidades específicas tenham acesso, complementar dos blocos em desenho universal para aprendizagem como elementos químicos da tabela periódica, amparados pela patente br 10 2020 022931 1, que podem ser acoplados às plataformas (89a, 89b). o produto possui um botão (97) para cada elemento da tabela periódica que, quando pressionado, aciona a narração e a transcrição, em linguagem libras e comum, de características do elemento ou da substância selecionada, tal como nome, número atômico, massa, período e família, classificação e algumas aplicações. a tela também exibe ilustrações de aplicações dos elementos. este produto resolve a incapacidade de os produtos existentes atenderem adequadamente a mais de um tipo de deficiência simultaneamente, viabilizando a aprendizagem da química, permitindo o estudo de substâncias químicas e permitindo o transporte entre salas ou instituições por ser portátil. o produto possui legendas (9, 10, 91, 94, 95) em linguagem comum e no sistema de escrita braille, bem como um bloco legenda (108), que permitem que o usuário interaja de maneira independente com o produto. a tela interativa (151) permite a configuração do dispositivo (escolha de idiomas, controle de volume, tempo de resposta ao clique, atualizações) bem como a conexão com outros dispositivos como celulares ou computadores via protocolo de comunicação bluetooth.

column12: MOLECULAR MARKER FOR DETECTING CERVICAL CANCER.
column13: Described is a diagnostic method of cervical cancer, which comprises: a) extracting the total RNA from a cervix biopsy sample in a human being; b) synthesising the cDNA from the total RNA, where said cDNA is used as a mould for performing a PCR in real time with a detection nucleotide probe which may perform a hybridisation under strict conditions with a target sequence or the complement thereof contained in the nucleotide sequence which encodes for the human protein or polypeptide of the subunit NaV1.6 of the sodium channels dependant on voltage, thus forming a stable hybrid for the probe: target detection; and c) determining if the hybrid is present in the sample, where the presence or absence of cervical cancer is determined by the identification and quantification of the probe:target hybrid, obtaining in such a manner the Ct values. In addition, an other method is described for the detection of the aforementioned disorders, which consists in a) having a cervix biopsy sample from a human being; b) processing said sample for being subjected to the immunohistochemical technique using an immunospecific antibody against a human protein or polypeptide of the subunit Nav1.6 of the sodium channels dependant on voltage; and c) detecting the formation of said immunological complex between the protein or polypeptide present in the sample, and the marked antibody.

column12: Framework for maintaining information security in computer networks
column13: A system is provided for controlling access to information technology assets in a computer network. The system includes a ticket manager server configured to generate tickets based on user data in a master database. A ticket manager client, resident on a workstation, is configured to receive tickets from the ticket manager server and distribute resource data obtained from the tickets to network security modules. The user data includes resource registers, each of which has a type field designating a particular security module, resource data for use by the designated security module, and an execution domain field that exclusively designates an execution environment in which the designated security module can use the resource data.
column15: ARCE VELLEGGIA IVAN FRANCISCO;;FUTORANSKY ARIEL;;RICHARTE GERARDO GABRIEL;;KARGIEMAN EMILIANO;;OCHOA CARLOS HERNAN

column12: TABELA PERIÓDICA UNIVERSAL INCLUSIVA E INTERATIVA
column13: TABELA PERIÓDICA UNIVERSAL INCLUSIVA E INTERATIVA. A TABELA PERIÓDICA UNIVERSAL INCLUSIVA E INTERATIVA. É um produto desenvolvido por meio dos conceitos do Universal Design for Learning (UDL) para o ensino e a aprendizagem da Química. Composto por uma maleta com duas tampas (1A, 1B), uma base central (2), um sistema de trava (3), duas plataformas (89A, 89B) e um sistema eletrônico (90A, 90B) dotado de alto-falantes (48) e uma tela sensível ao toque (151), o produto permite que estudantes sem deficiência, da Educação Especial ou com necessidades específicas tenham acesso, simultaneamente, a uma série de informações referentes aos elementos químicos ou substâncias, seja pela narração de áudios específicos, pela transcrição em linguagem Libras ou ainda, pelo uso complementar dos BLOCOS EM DESENHO UNIVERSAL PARA APRENDIZAGEM COMO ELEMENTOS QUÍMICOS DA TABELA PERIÓDICA, amparados pela patente BR 10 2020 022931 1, que podem ser acoplados às plataformas (89A, 89B). O produto possui um botão (97) para cada elemento da Tabela Periódica que, quando pressionado, aciona a narração e a transcrição, em linguagem Libras e comum, de características do elemento ou da substância selecionada, tal como nome, número atômico, massa, período e família, classificação e algumas aplicações. A tela também exibe ilustrações de aplicações dos elementos. Este produto resolve a incapacidade de os produtos existentes atenderem adequadamente a mais de um tipo de deficiência simultaneamente, viabilizando a aprendizagem da Química, permitindo o estudo de substâncias químicas e permitindo o transporte entre salas ou instituições por ser portátil. O produto possui legendas (9, 10, 91, 94, 95) em linguagem comum e no sistema de escrita Braille, bem como um Bloco Legenda (108), que permitem que o usuário interaja de maneira independente com o produto. A tela interativa (151) permite a configuração do dispositivo (escolha de idiomas, controle de volume, tempo de resposta ao clique, atualizações) bem como a conexão com outros dispositivos como celulares ou computadores via protocolo de comunicação Bluetooth.

column12: ENZYMATIC SYNTHESIS OF ANTIOXIDANT HYDROXYTYROSOL
column13: The reaction occurs in a medium buffered with phosphate in an aqueous medium, at neutral pH and at room temperature. Hence, the reaction medium consists of: tyrosol, as precursor (commercial) mushroom tyrosinase to catalyze the process and vitamin C in excess. Reaction starts after initial shaking. The reaction stops when the concentration of the initial tyrosol is exhausted. In order for the reaction to continue, it will suffice to add more tyrosol (always ensuring that the vitamin C/tyrosol ratio is more than 1). Once the desired concentration of hydroxytyrosol is obtained, it is filtered. The enzyme with molecular weight over twice the size of the pore is retained in the filter and can be used once again. This first extract, which is very enriched in antioxidant hydroxytyrosol with a high antioxidant capacity (in the present case, in combination with vitamin C), can already be used as a food additive.

column12: SINTESIS ENZIMATICA DEL ANTIOXIDANTE HIDROXITIROSOL.
column13: Síntesis enzimática del antioxidante hidroxitirosol. La reacción transcurre en un medio tamponado con fosfato en medio acuoso, a pH neutro, y a temperatura ambiente. El medio de reacción, se compone por tanto de: tirosol, como precursor; tirosinasa de champiñón (comercial) para catalizar el proceso y vitamina C en exceso. Tras una agitación inicial, la reacción comienza. Cuando la concentración de tirosol inicial se agote la reacción se para. Para que continúe basta con añadir más tirosol (siempre cuidando que la relación vitamina C/tirosol sea mayor que 1). Cuando se obtenga la concentración de hidroxitirosol deseada, se filtra por una membrana. La enzima, de peso molecular más del doble del tamaño de poro, queda retenida en el filtro, y puede ser de nuevo reutilizada. Este primer extracto muy enriquecido en antioxidante hidroxitirosol, con una alta capacidad antioxidante, (en este caso, en combinación con vitamina C), ya es susceptible de utilizarse como aditivo alimentario.

column12: AEROHEATING PROTECTION FOR A MISSILE ELECTRO - OPTICAL SEEKER
column13: This invention advances the related state-of-the-art by eliminating the physical EO window used by electro-optical imaging infrared seekers for tactical missiles and high-altitude endo-atmospheric interceptors, widely employed in integrated defense systems. This invention increases the probability of intercepting exo-atmospheric ballistic warheads by exo-atmospheric interceptors, and eliminates the existing altitude "gap" of interception, as well as the geographical limitations posed by the mesospheric Noctilucent Clouds. The problem of protecting an imaging EO sensor from aeroheating is solved in this invention by a special purpose device which is enabled immediately after the nose cone ejection event. The role of said device is to augment the sensor fixed sunshade and cavity lengths in the forward direction, and by doing so, the resulting new cavity enables the optimal injection of an optically inert gas into the new extended cavity in front of the sensor, thus effectively blocking the entry of the compressed hot air into the sensor cavity, while simultaneously avoiding any adverse effects of inducing flow instabilities in the flow as well as the disturbance of the injected gas flow on sensor structures. Having a greater length for the hot gas to penetrate, eliminates also the penetration of suspended particles in oncoming air stream.

column12: Protección contra el calentamiento aerodinámico para cabeza buscadora electroóptica de misiles
column13: Un dispositivo de protección para una cabeza buscadora EO de misiles que comprende una pantalla fija (1) que puede estar montada rodeando un sensor de cabeza buscadora EO, formando la pantalla fija (1) una cavidad (7), caracterizado por comprender: al menos una pantalla desplegable (10) dispuesta para ser desplazada de manera telescópica con respecto a la pantalla fija (1) entre una primera posición, en la que la al menos una pantalla desplegable (10) sustancialmente no sobresale de la pantalla fija (1), y una segunda posición, en la que la al menos una pantalla desplegable (10) está desplegada con respecto a la pantalla fija (1) creando así una cavidad de mayor longitud (7) con respecto a la primera posición, al menos un receptáculo (15) para un gas de presurización ópticamente inerte, en el que en la segunda posición, el gas ópticamente inerte puede ser inyectado en el interior de un espacio encarado hacia adelante del sensor dentro de la cavidad (7), formando un patrón de flujo altamente estable (9).

column12: Enzymatic synthesis of antioxidant hydroxytyrosol
column13: The reaction occurs in a medium buffered with phosphate in an aqueous medium, at neutral pH and at room temperature. Hence, the reaction medium consists of: tyrosol, as precursor; (commercial) mushroom tyrosinase to catalyze the process and vitamin C in excess. Reaction starts after initial shaking. The reaction stops when the concentration of the initial tyrosol is exhausted. In order for the reaction to continue, it will suffice to add more tyrosol (always ensuring that the vitamin C/tyrosol ratio is more than 1). Once the desired concentration of hydroxytyrosol is obtained, it is filtered. The enzyme with molecular weight over twice the size of the pore is retained in the filter and can be used once again. This first extract, which is very enriched in antioxidant hydroxytyrosol with a high antioxidant capacity (in the present case, in combination with vitamin C), can already be used as a food additive.

column12: COMPOSICIONES Y MÉTODOS PARA INHIBIR LA FLORACIÓN DE LA CANA DE AZÚCAR
column13: La floración de la cana de azúcar puede inhibirse cuando se aplica sobre el follaje, composiciones que contienen cierta cantidad de 1,3-bis-(2,2,2-tricloro-1-hidroxietil) urea con o sin 2,2,2-tricloro-1-1 hidroxietil urea, convenientemente formuladas, después que el cultivo ha "cerrado" y antes de que se forme el primordio floral.

column12: MECANISMO PARA REGULAR LA ACTIVIDAD DE LA ALDOSA REDUCTASA Y PARA PREVENIR LA FORMACION DE CATARATAS EN DIABETES MELLITUS, A PARTIR DE LA ASOCIACION DE LA ALDOSA REDUCTASA CON LA TUBULINA Y DE LA UTILIZACION DE 3-NITRO-L-TIROSINA Y TIROSINA
column13: Mecanismo para la regulación de la actividad AR por Tub en condiciones de diabetes o elevada concentración de glucosa, a través de la regulación de la cantidad de complejo Tub/AR formado, el cual puede ser regulado a su vez por drogas como la 3-NTyr o la Tyr, que impidan la asociación directa entre estas dos proteínas y que mostraron ser capaces de impedir la formación del complejo Tub/AR, de activar la enzima AR y de prevenir la aparición de cataratas en ratas diabéticas. En el mecanismo descripto, las elevadas concentraciones intracelulares de glucosa actúan como un disparador de un estrés oxidativo/nitrosativo que conduce a la generación de especies reactivas de oxígeno y nitrógeno y a la nitración de la Tyr libre para producir 3-NTyr, la cual es rápidamente incorporada a la Tub para formar el isótopo de Tub 3-nitrotirosinado, que es el que preferentemente interacciona con la AR para formar el complejo Tub/AR. De esta forma se produce un incremento en la concentración de complejo Tub/AR y cuando éste polimeriza para formar MT la AR se activa reduciendo el exceso de glucosa a sorbitol, el cual induce la polimerización de más cantidad de Tub en MT, generándose de esta forma un círculo vicioso retroalimentado positivamente entre el incremento de la actividad AR y la formación de MT mientras persistan las condiciones de elevada glucosa. Como consecuencia de este circuito retroalimentado, mayor cantidad de Tub acetilada llega a la membrana plasmática para asociarse con la NKA e inhibirla.

column12: TACHO DE BASURA COMPRESOR CON COMPARTIMIENTO PARA RECICLAJE
column13: Un tacho de basura compresor con compartimento para reciclaje, comprendido por un deposito de forma preferentemente triangular, aunque puede variar su forma; donde se realizara la compresion de residuos generales a traves de un sistema de hidraulico-mecanico, el cual consistira en una camara de compresion que, accionada mediante una palanca giratoria, se realizara la compresion con la placa deslizable. Al exterior del deposito se encontrara compartimentos exteriores de diferentes formas y tamanos para el deposito de residuos reciclables.
